The teenager was allegedly murdered by her stepfather this week. Courtesy #DStv403 PINETOWN - The memorial service of Ayakha Jiyane took place in Pinetown, KwaZulu-Natal on Friday. The teenager was murdered, allegedly by her stepfather, this week. The man has since been arrested for the murder of her three siblings as well. READ: KZN man suspected of killing his 4 children in custody Pupils at Pinetown Girls’ High gave Jiyane a round of applause, in celebration of her life at the school remembrance ceremony. Meanwhile, murder-accused Sibusiso Mpungose appeared in court where he abandoned his bail application. The case has been adjourned until 9 October. Mpungose will remain in custody throughout the trial.